items.title: Healthcare stocks rally, US govt. to pay more to Medicare plans
items.description: UnitedHealth (UNH), Humana (HUM), and CVS Health (CVS) rally in extended-hours trading on news that the US government will pay more than previously proposed to Medicare Advantage providers. Julie Hyman breaks down the details on Market Domination Overtime. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here.

items.title: Medicare Advantage’s diagnosing tactics made insurers like UnitedHealthGroup $33 billion richer
items.description: Medicare Advantage plans are paid more for sicker members and less for healthier members, which provides an incentive for MA plans to report as many diagnoses as legitimately possible.
